{\*\generator Msftedit 5.41.15.1515;}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\b\f0\fs20 Much of your online programming logic will probably be executed when a user enters or leaves a field. For instance, when a user enters a field you may want to display some helpful text or automatically pop up a list of choices. When the user leaves a field, you may want to execute a function to do some computations, or validate what the user just entered.\par
\par
This sort of logic is entered in the \cf2 Control Prefix\cf1  and \cf2 Control Suffix \cf1 logic units.\par
\par
In this example, the Field3 Control has both prefix and suffix logic units. You will get a message when the cursor enters Field3, and another when the cursor leaves Field3. However, you will not get a message if you click "past" Field3, by entering Field2 and then clicking on Field4.\par
}

